ted and the poster will be banned.<br><br>8)  Posters that have demonstrated over a period of time to have no desire to contribute positively to the community may be removed if the admin or moderators feel that removal would be in the greater interest of the community.  Such individuals may be more commonly referred to in internet lingo at 'trolls' or 'baiters'.  Due to the nature of these bans, they are subject to review, and may be made temporary or reversed at the discretion of the administrators.<br><br>9) The administrator and moderators are allowed to delete and modify posts/threads and/or ban you without giving you, or anyone else, an explanation. <br><br>10) The administrator and moderators may add, change, update or remove rules as needed. When new rules are added and the date of your new post is after this date, you are agreeing to the new posted/updated rules. It is your responsibility to know the rules.<br><br>11) The administrator of the VCC witholds all rights to moderate the forums within the spirit of the rules above.  All actionable offenses and violations will be given due consideration by 'common sense', and may be punished more or less harshly depending on the severity of the act and the interpretation of the act by the administrators.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Repeatedly breaking the rules could lead to your being banned. This will be viewed on a case by case basis.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uanikacrystalwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anika Crystalwind</A> at: 8/24/02 2:26:54 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=48.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommuni